Description: Head of Isis with diadem and long curls, right. (obverse)
Eagle standing on thunderbolt with wings closed, left looking right; on shoulder, cornucopia. (reverse)
State: Associated with: Kingdom of Egypt Ancient Greece and Rome: Kingdom of Egypt
Curator's comments: Attributed to Ptolemy VI Philopator I in Seton-Williams 1969.
